
How to Create Environments

1- windows search ==> cmd ==> open Propmt (Run as administrator)
2- conda list ==> to check all the packages
3- we want to make these environmets: (we already have a default environment)
   tf_1.9 : Python: 3.6
             Tensorflow: 1.9
             CUDA: 9
             cuDNN:7
   tf_1.13 : Python: 3.6
             Tensorflow: 1.13
             CUDA: 10
             cuDNN:7.4
   tf_2.1 : Python: 3.7
             Tensorflow: 2.1
             CUDA: 10.1
             cuDNN:7.4

to create tf_1.9
1- conda create --name tf_1.13 python=3.6
2- conda env list ==> gives a list of environments
3- activate tf_1.9 ==> to activate tf_1.9
4- conda list ==> gives a list of packages in new environment
5- conda install tensorflow-gpu=1.9
6- conda list ==> shows tensorflow 1.9 installed

to create tf_1.13
1- deactivate ==> returns to the basic environment
2- conda create --name tf_1.13 python=3.6
3- conda env list ==> gives a list of environments
4- activate tf_1.13 ==> to activate tf_1.13
5- conda list ==> gives a list of packages in new environment
6- conda install tensorflow-gpu=1.13
7- conda list ==> shows tensorflow 1.13 installed

to create tf_2.1
1- deactivate ==> returns to the basic environment
2- conda create --name tf_2.1 python=3.7
3- conda env list ==> gives a list of environments
4- activate tf_2.1 ==> to activate tf_2.1
5- conda list ==> gives a list of packages in new environment
6- conda install tensorflow-gpu=2.1
7- conda list ==> shows tensorflow 2.1 installed

Use Python Interpreter to select the environment.

in conda prompt:
1- conda activate env_name
2- conda install spyder
3- spyder



